728165f-a.text: Vernon Boulevard, east side, north from 30th Drive to 30th Road. The first house is part of the old General Ebenezer Stevens House, also known as the Albert Gallatin House. Other views of this pre-Revolutionary home are under the 30th Road location. The two frame dwellings to the left of the Stevens House are on the north side of 30th Road and in the left background is the very old Greenoak House, also known as the Mrs. Blonson House. P.L. Sperr March 14, 1931
